{"TopicId":163943,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"On rails rover rotation","CreatedByName":"maja","CreatedById":168379,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-01T08:52:20Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"maja","CreatedById":168379,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-01T08:52:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a rover, which is moved when on rails, and I need to rotate it in a such way, that it\u0027s always up (perpendicular to the surface slope will be better, but up is enough), when you switch to it. Something what\u0027s Hyperedit do, when lands rover and rotation is switched on. I looked into the Hyperedits code and tried the whole day to get some result, but now I\u0027m lost in Vectors, Quaternions and Transforms. Can someone point me in the right direction?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks a lot \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-08-02T10:17:02Z\u0022 title=\u002208/02/2017 10:17  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 2, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by maja\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ThreePounds","CreatedById":116058,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-01T08:58:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t help you directly, but\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/133082-13-krash-kerbal-ramification-artificial-simulation-hub-simulation-mod-for-ksp-cost-settings-have-been-change/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EKRASH\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0has a function that allows vessels to be placed on an arbitrary planetary surface. Maybe you can have a look at how he solved the problem? The source code is\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/linuxgurugamer/KRASH\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehere.\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: it must be somewhere \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/linuxgurugamer/KRASH/blob/master/Source/View/Lander.cs\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E or in an adjacent part of the code.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-08-01T08:59:58Z\u0022 title=\u002208/01/2017 08:59  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 1, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Three_Pounds\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wasml","CreatedById":120438,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-02T00:49:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBon Voyage also did something similar.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/147876-ksp-122-bon-voyage-0120-make-your-wheels-rolling-2017-03-18/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maja","CreatedById":168379,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-02T10:11:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/116058-three_pounds/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022116058\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/116058-three_pounds/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Three_Pounds\u003C/a\u003E I\u0027ll looked on it and it\u0027s the same code as Hyperedit. For active vessel. But thanks anyway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/120438-wasml/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\